The missing invariant is:

Invariant 11 — Time, Delay, and Cadence

Every complex system runs on finite update rates and propagation delays. Signals arrive late. Actions take time to take effect. Learning lags reality. Memory decays. Policies go stale. Delays create:
	•	overshoot / oscillation
	•	phase shifts (“the system looks like it changed its mind”)
	•	hysteresis (path-dependence / “sticky states”)
	•	false causality (you credit the wrong intervention)

This is the invariant that quietly explains why smart systems still blow up.

